http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Visakhapatnam/Enthusiasm-marks-%E2%80%98Sankranti-Milan%E2%80%99/article14003040.ece

Rangoli, Haridasu show and kite-flying carrying mugshot of Prime Minister Narendra Modi marked ‘Sankranti Milan’ celebrations by Bharatiya Janata Party here on Saturday.Hosted by MP and party State president K. Haribabu at his office near Appughar, the event was attended among others by Union Urban Development Minister M. Venkaiah Naidu, Narsapur MP Gokaraju Gangaraju, MLAs P. Vishnu Kumar Raju and Palla Srinivasa Rao and a group of foreigners.There was enthusiasm all over. Serving traditional food like ariselu and pulihora marked the occasion. Gangireddus were also displayed to add colour to the event.Speaking on the occasion, Mr. Venkaiah Naidu said due to climate change the timing of harvest festival was adversely hit. He said “as we have inherited legacy of our forefathers, we have to continue our rich traditions.”